  The number of vertices of a polytope associated to the Knapsack integer programming problem is shown to be small. An algorithm for finding these vertices is discussed. [1] L.G. Khachian A polynomial algorithm in linear programming Dokl. Akad. Nauk. SSSR, 244 (1979), pp. 1093–1096 [2] P. Gács, L. Lovász Khachiyan's algorithm for linear programming Math. Programming Study, 14 (1981), pp. 61–68 [3] H.W. Lenstra, Jr., Integer programming with a fixed number of variables, Preprint, Mathematisch Centrum. [4] P. McMullen On the upper bound conjecture for convex polytopes J. Combin. Theory (B), 10 (1971), pp. 187–200 The research of this author was carried out while he was in receipt of a Science Research Council Research Studentship Copyright © 1983 Published by Elsevier B.V.